rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week I only have to clean my garage and the lawn for a home appraisal.  In theory I'd like to clean out my closet, although I'm not sure I'll get it done. However if I manage to accomplish all of these I will definitely feel a sense of personal achievement.
critical_positive: She was very easy to talk to and we discussed common topics such as our employment, and travel and the effect of COVID-19 on our personal lives and that of our families.  She seemed easy-going and we both kind of rolled with any issues that we came across and laughed plenty during the conversation. So the fact that it was lighthearted was probably what worked the best.
critical_negative: I really don't think there was anything that didn't work in our conversation. We seemed to find common ground on almost every subject, even including those where we discussed vocabulary native to our areas that other areas might not be familiar with. I feel like we both saw it as a positive rather than something that didnt work. It seemed like we both enjoyed learning about the other.

rest_of_day_open: I imagine that I will spend quite a bit of time working around the house this weekend.  I need to do some grocery shopping, some laundry, and I would like to decorate for the holidays.  Other than that I may see some close friends, so I think that will be a good relaxing time.
critical_positive: I think that we were both forthcoming and willing to offer our own thoughts and experiences that allowed us to relate to each other.  We are similar ages and living through the same things which are affecting our lives.  My conversation partner was nice and had a nice smile that helped make me comfortable.
critical_negative: There was one moment where the video lagged very badly and that made me nervous that something would go wrong and we wouldn't be able to complete the conversation, but, it actually worked very well after that.  My conversation partner's video quality was not the best, but that did not hinder our conversation.
